Pong brainstorm
Requirements:
The game must start - functional mandatory
It must allow a single user to play against a cpu

User must be able to control the paddle to go up and down

Game should allow two players to play against each other

A score must be updated each time the player scores on the opposing side’s goal

The game must operate a ball that can be bounced with moveable paddles on both sides

The game must have bounds detection for the paddle

Player should be allowed to choose between cpu difficulties: easy, medium, and hard

Can add power ups that can augment 
player’s capabilities: faster paddle, bigger paddle, powerful paddle

Can leave room for more power ups along the way of production and future updates

Can allow faster game speed to allow higher difficulty/ more engaging gameplay

Has to have a menu with choices of: play, settings, difficulty, and quit

Settings at the bare minimum can adjust the game speed and graphical settings
